last_episode_to_air.name: Grand Finale Variety Extravaganza: Part 2
last_episode_to_air.overview: After their final Runway, Guest Judge Connie Britton visits the Untucked Lounge. But as the Queens prepare to meet their fates on the main stage, uncertainty looms. Tonight, any of these Queens could make the Top Three and take home the Crown!

name: RuPaul's Drag Race All Stars: UNTUCKED
original_name: RuPaul's Drag Race All Stars: UNTUCKED
overview: An access-all-areas pass to the drama that you didn't see on the runway. See what happens behind the scenes when the queens let their tucks breathe... and let their emotions flow.

seasons.name: Season 2
seasons.overview: This season of Untucked featured the queens' backstage deliberation, a segment with the Lip Sync Assassin, their votes for the next eliminated queen, and a little interview of Michelle Visage and the eliminated queen.

episodes.name: It Takes Two
episodes.overview: The queens get riled up when one queen storms off after harsh critiques from her peers.

episodes.name: RuPaul's Gaff-In
episodes.overview: The queens are surprised by a video message that leave many of the queens emotional.

episodes.name: Queens Behaving Badly
episodes.overview: The remaining All Stars bicker back stage about comments that were made on the runway.

episodes.name: All Star Girl Groups
episodes.overview: The remaining All Stars are greeted by their fellow band mates in the Untucked lounge.

episodes.name: Dynamic Drag Duos
episodes.overview: The remaining two teams get an earful from one queen until they get surprise questions from fans.

episodes.name: The Grand Finale
episodes.overview: For the first time ever, RuPaul surprises the queens in the lounge and has a final heart to heart with them before deciding the winner of All Stars.

episodes.name: All Star Variety Extravaganza
episodes.overview: After the All Stars perform in a variety show, Jujubee spills on the hostilities between Derrick Barry and India Ferrah, and the queens deliberate about the bottom two.

episodes.name: I'm In Love!
episodes.overview: After the All Stars' girl-group performances, the judges reveal their celebrity crushes, Miz Cracker grapples with her reputation, and Alexis Mateo gets emotional over voting.

episodes.name: Get A Room!
episodes.overview: After the All Stars design hotel suites, Mayhem Miller opens up about her personal struggles, Nicole Byer acts out dirty charades, and a lip sync assassin prepares for battle.

episodes.name: SheMZ
episodes.overview: After the All Stars improv on a TMZ-style show, Blair St. Clair reflects on being typecast, a lip sync assassin returns, and the eliminated queen opens up to Michelle Visage.

episodes.name: Snatch Game of Love
episodes.overview: After the Snatch Game of Love, Miz Cracker investigates potential backstabbing, an assassin makes her entrance, and Michelle Visage gets the tea on the messiness backstage.

episodes.name: The Charles Family Backyard Ball
episodes.overview: After a family barbecue-themed ball, RuPaul and her sisters kiki, questions linger about whether Alexis Mateo campaigned against Shea Coulee, and a lip sync assassin returns.

episodes.name: Stand-Up Smackdown
episodes.overview: After the All Stars perform stand-up, Blair St. Clair defends her set, Jujubee gets emotional over voting, and Michelle Visage has a one-on-one with the eliminated queen.

episodes.name: Clap Back!
episodes.overview: After the All Stars perform a finale number and reconvene with the eliminated queens, India Ferrah and Alexis Mateo make peace, and the Top Three queens prepare for their final lip sync.

2.name: Season 2
2.overview: This season of Untucked featured the queens' backstage deliberation, a segment with the Lip Sync Assassin, their votes for the next eliminated queen, and a little interview of Michelle Visage and the eliminated queen.

episodes.name: All Star Variety Extravaganza
episodes.overview: Back in the Werkroom, after a glittering All Stars Variety Show, the queens reunite for the first time to untuck and spill the T. They anticipate the upcoming season which promises to be legendary, right out of the gate!

episodes.name: The Blue Ball
episodes.overview: After the first elimination the pressure is already on, the queens untuck and kiki about which All Star was the belle of the Ball and who dropped the ball altogether. They discuss voting strategies, and a friendship is put to the ultimate test!

episodes.name: Side Hustles
episodes.overview: The All Stars untuck and open up about the toughest elimination yet. Two past season sisters confront an old grudge, can they reinvest in a future of renewed drag sisterhood?

episodes.name: Halftime Headliners
episodes.overview: After an All Star studded stadium halftime show, the queens untuck and dish on their experiences from celebrities to go-go boys. Everyone slayed in the spotlight, but despite the lovefest, one queen must still sashay away.

episodes.name: Pink Table Talk
episodes.overview: The All Stars can make opposing patterns mesh, but it doesn’t mean their personalities will mesh too. The voting process has tensions flaring and certain queens struggle to cool down and get out of their heads, but the Tea just keeps flowing.

episodes.name: Ru-Merican Horror Story: Coven Girl
episodes.overview: RuPaul’s Drag Race All Stars: Untucked! is the access-all-areas pass to the drama that you didn’t see on the runway. See what happens behind the scenes when the queens let their tucks breathe… and let their emotions flow.

episodes.name: Show Up Queen
episodes.overview: Our All Stars untuck to spill the Tea, honey, about their personal connection to the legendary RuPaul herself. They gag over how Ru has affected their lives in and out of the werkroom. The Tea is spilled and the shenanigans are brought.

episodes.name: Snatch Game of Love
episodes.overview: The All Stars untuck, kiki and sip some well-deserved bubbly to celebrate the Pop Art of it all. As the competition narrows, jaws are dropped and dream bubbles get popped.

episodes.name: Drag Tots
episodes.overview: After tooning out in the Drag Tots challenge, the final 5 queens are spilling all the hot Tea. When Ru makes the rules you never know what you're gonna get except for twisted. So don't get caught without your wig on!

episodes.name: Rudemption Lip-Sync Smackdown
episodes.overview: The Big Ruveal has the All Stars Queens gagging on a twist none of them saw coming, but there's still time for final tête-à-têtes in the spirit of All Stars Drag sisterhood.

episodes.name: The Charisma, Uniqueness, Nerve and Talent Monologues
episodes.overview: One All Star proved herself by fighting her way back into the competition, but can she Shantay and stay? Heading into the battle of a Fierce Final Four means it's time to untuck and leave it all on the runway.

episodes.name: This is Our Country
episodes.overview: The Final Four All Stars reflect upon their growth. It's time for all but one legendary All Star to untuck and pack it all up in this Untucked finale.

episodes.name: Legends
episodes.overview: Backstage after their first performance and runway, 8 competing champions speculate about how new rules and potential alliances may may affect the season ahead. Guest Judge and Superfan Cameron Diaz visits the werkroom to kiki with the queens.

episodes.name: Snatch Game
episodes.overview: After an epic Snatch Game, the queens are wondering who's on top, and who's getting blocked? Plus, a rousing game of "Kiki, Kai Kai, Marry" reveals some surprises about how the Queens really feel about each other. Guest Judge and fashion icon Daphne Guiness pops by to share some of her own style secrets.

episodes.name: The Realness of Fortune Ball
episodes.overview: As the Queens gush about each others' gorgeous ball looks and kiki about whose drag they would mop, the conversation takes an emotional turn. Guest Judge Kirby Baptiste-Howell talks fashion and gardening during her visit to the werkroom and scores herself an invite to the Drag Queen BBQ.

episodes.name: Fairytale Justice
episodes.overview: One queen is riding high after this week's challenge, but another gets salty when the group agrees that she'll be the next to get blocked; guest Judge Jeffrey Bowyer-Chapman visits and shares how Drag Race has affected the entire world.

episodes.name: Dragulation Speeches
episodes.overview: After their Draguation Speeches, the Queens share how their high school experiences shaped who they are today; a twist in the rules has everyone speculating how things will play out; Guest Judge Nikki Glaser joins the queens for a chat about passion.

episodes.name: Total Ru-quest Live
episodes.overview: The Queens reflect on their runway and share how Dolly Parton has inspired them. One queen's frustrations lead to an very stress relief moment for all the girls. And, just before the lip sync, two queens share a heartfelt moment, while another has an epiphany. Plus, Guest Judge Tove Lo talks to the queens about songwriting and style.

episodes.name: Legendary Legend Looks
episodes.overview: The competition heats up as the Queens realize that everyone is a threat, and this is still anyone's game. Legendary Guest Judge Betsey Johnson brings her quirky energy to the werkroom, shares stories of her epic life and offers insight about how to make it as an artist.

episodes.name: Santa's School for Girls
episodes.overview: The Queens cool off after the hottest runway yet. Following the acting challenge, the performances continue in the werkroom with the Queens serving up spot-on impressions of Queens from past seasons - and each other!

episodes.name: Dance Like Drag Queen
episodes.overview: As the end of the competition draws near, the Queens reminisce about the Queens they have blocked. Guest Judge Ben Platt stops by, the queens grill him about his nail polish, his boyfriend and his own possible drag future.

episodes.name: The Kennedy Davenport Center Honors Hall of Shade
episodes.overview: After an illuminating runway, a surprise guest awaits the Queens in the werkroom. Then, Guest Judge Ronan Farrow visits to ask some probing questions, and then the queens ask a few of their own. And finally, a game of "Two Truths and a Lie" uncovers a juicy secret that has everyone gooped!

episodes.name: Drag Race Gives Back Variety Extravaganza
episodes.overview: The penultimate episode has the Queens gagging over their variety show performances. Guest Judge Hannah Einbinder fangirls over the ladies - and the feeling is mutual. And, things get turnt when the girls play "Tower of Truth" and some piping hot tea is spilled!

episodes.name: Lip Sync LaLaPaRuza
episodes.overview: After an emotional moment with Ru on the main stage, the Queens head to the werkroom to get ready for the LaLaparuza Lip-Sync Smackdown for the Crown; the stakes couldn't be higher, as the Queens watch each other battle for big money.

episodes.name: The Fame Games
episodes.overview: After an emotional deliberation and a visit from guest judge Indina Menzel, the Queens realize that sending their competitors home is harder than expected.

episodes.name: It's RDR Live!
episodes.overview: In their second deliberation of the season, the All Stars discuss whether personal relationships or track record matter most when determining who goes home. And, the Fame Games kick off, featuring the runway looks of eliminated queens.

episodes.name: The Supermarket Ball
episodes.overview: After the Supermarket Ball, the Queens are in their feelings, and one contemplates a drastic decision. Guest judge and pop star Jojo Siwa kikis with the Queens about the importance of being yourself.

episodes.name: Screen Queens
episodes.overview: This week, the Queens are judged as a group, which has Queens pointing fingers and scrambling to save themselves. Guest judge Maude Apatow visits the Werk Room to fangirl over the All Stars.

episodes.name: Snatch Game of Love
episodes.overview: After a shocking turn of events, the Queens are left wondering how it will affect the game. Guest Judges Bowen Yang and Matt Rogers visit the Werk Room and share what Drag Race means to them.

episodes.name: JOAN: The Unauthorized Rusical!
episodes.overview: Deliberations continue to get more difficult as the Queens struggle to decide who should get the chop. Guest Judge Adam Shankman visits the Queens to celebrate the success of the Rusical challenge.

episodes.name: Forensic Queens
episodes.overview: After an emotional week, one of the Queens finds herself in the bottom again, while another tries to win favor with her fellow All Stars. Guest Judge and actress Javicia Leslie visits the Werk Room.

episodes.name: You’re a Winner Baby!
episodes.overview: As one All Star reconsiders a promise she made, the remaining contestants fight to keep their spot in the competition. Guest judge and Incubus frontman Brandon Boyd pops into the Werk Room.

episodes.name: Carson Kressley, This is Your Gay Life
episodes.overview: The All Stars are excited to receive words of encouragement from loved ones back home, but with so few queens left, figuring out who to eliminate is intense. Will one queen’s strategy to stay in the game pay off?

episodes.name: The Letter “L”
episodes.overview: After the makeover challenge, the Queens reflect on their amazing experiences with their new lesbian sisters. And Guest Judge Zooey Deschanel visits to talk nerves with the All Stars.

episodes.name: The Fame Games Variety Extravaganza
episodes.overview: While the finalists jockey for the crown, the competition revs up for the returning queens vying for the title, “Queen of the Fame Games!” Plus, Guest Judge Ego Nwodim visits with the Queens.

episodes.name: Grand Finale
episodes.overview: The Queens of All Stars 8 celebrate a gagworthy season. The Top Queens prepare for one ,final performance, and everyone wonders who will be the next Queen to be inducted into the Drag Race Hall of Fame!

episodes.name: Drag Queens Save The World
episodes.overview: The Queens are excited to raise money for their charities and showcase their talents on the mainstage! They speculate about who'll win the first Benefactress Badges of the season, and who'll get cut off. Guest Judge Keke Palmer pops in for a kiki!

episodes.name: The Paint Ball
episodes.overview: As the All Stars gag over each other's Paint Ball looks, they reflect on their walk-throughs with RuPaul. The Queens keep the arty party going with a raucous game of "Win, Lose or Bra." Guest Judge Stephanie Hsu visits.

episodes.name: Snatch Game of Love
episodes.overview: After The Snatch Game of Love, the Queens are gooped thinking about how this week's twist could impact the game - and their sisterhood. Guest Judge Anitta shows up to turn the party.

episodes.name: Smokin' Hot Firefighter Makeover
episodes.overview: After the makeovers, the Queens kiki with their hunky firemen. Guest Judges John & T.J. Osborne visit, and T.J. discuss the struggle of being gay in country music. And as a bonus, Firefighter Bradley shares his own extra-special party skills.

episodes.name: Property Queens
episodes.overview: As the All Stars struggle with the stress of the competition, Guest Judge Alec Mapa drops by to boost their spirits. Later, the Queens kiki and serve up impressions of past Ru girls and each other - until one cuts too close to home.

episodes.name: The National Drag Convention Roast
episodes.overview: After a surprise visit with Bob the Drag Queen, the All Stars get serious and discuss how they plan to use their platforms politically. Then, when Guest Judge Ruta Lee joins the queens, things get genuinely emotional and heartfelt.

episodes.name: Meeting In The Ladies Room
episodes.overview: After the Queens rave about acting opposite Mama Ru, one All Star uses her math skills to avoid getting snipped! Guest Judge Colton Haynes visits the Untucked Lounge, and a message from Drag Race Royalty brings one Queen to tears.

episodes.name: Make Your Own Kind Of Rusic
episodes.overview: After weeks of feeling out of sorts, one Queen opens up to her sisters. An emotional message from home gets the All Stars talking about their love lives. And guest judge Jeremy Scott dazzles in the Untucked Lounge.

episodes.name: Rosemarie's Baby Shower: The Rusical
episodes.overview: The All Stars praise each other for their sickening Rusical performances. Messages from home lead one Queen to discuss her journey of family acceptance. Guest Judge Kristine W, stops by and serenades the All Stars.

episodes.name: Lip Sync LaLaPaRuza Smackdown
episodes.overview: Two Queens prepare for their final battle in the Lip Sync Lalaparuza Smackdown. After they leave it all on the stage, the All Stars celebrate the winner and anticipate the final push towards the finale.

episodes.name: Grand Finale Variety Extravaganza: Part 1
episodes.overview: On an extra-special episode, crew members-turned-queens kiki in the Untucked Lounge. They dish about working on the show, and share what they really think of the queens! Ts Madison pops by to find out more.

episodes.name: Grand Finale Variety Extravaganza: Part 2
episodes.overview: After their final Runway, Guest Judge Connie Britton visits the Untucked Lounge. But as the Queens prepare to meet their fates on the main stage, uncertainty looms. Tonight, any of these Queens could make the Top Three and take home the Crown!
